RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AUNT OPAL sent for lead three deep on the backstretch, continued three deep till entering the turn, went two wide dueling with ISLAND LIFE on the turn, inched away entering the lane and kept under a strong drive to the wire. ISLAND LIFE dueled for lead along the inside on the backstretch, continued along the inside on the turn, entered lane in range, battled to the wire while giving way grudginly. FLAG SALUTE chased pace two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, entered lane in range and kept to task in the lane to hold show. QUEEN VERRAZANO stalked pace along the inside on the backstretch, continued to save ground on the turn, eased out into the two path midway through the turn, entered lane in the three path and made mild progress late. FLASHY PASS away well sent to contend for pace early, had to settle for a chasing inside position, continued to save ground on the turn and failed to respond in the lane. LOUD FUSAICHI off bit slow, stalked pace off the rail, continued two to three wide on the turn and failed to threaten in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Loud Fusaichi
ENTRY.COMMENT: off bit slow, stalked 2-3wide, no threat

RACE.FOOTNOTES: NENE ROMANO chased leader two wide on the backstretch, continued to chase on the turn, made bold move late on the turn, shook clear and proved best. COUSIN NIECEY stalked pace three wide on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn, entered lane three wide and finished well three wide. MY SWEET MARY stalked between rivals on the backstretch, continued between on the turn and bested rest in the lane. VEGAS DREAM sent to lead on the backstretch, cleared into the turn, headed heading into the lane, and tired in upper stretch. LIBERTY LIBERTY stalked inside along the backstretch, continued along the inside, on the turn and took up midway through the turn when rival came in, and coasted into the lane.
